#1 Rectal cancer
Discussed evaluation with Mrs. Sturges. Her husband was in the waiting room, and she requested she be seen alone. Discussed reasoning behind the EUS procedure scheduled for tomorrow. I do not think we need to repeat a full colonoscopy here.  However, I have specifically requested our endoscopy colleagues to look at the area in the sigmoid that had inflammation as well as these other polyps from 25 to 30 cm in addition to tattooing distal to the rectal tumor.  We will have her outside CT-scan reviewed here.  I may decide to add a liver ultrasound as her CT was done without contrast to get a good view of the liver if this is indicated.  We will get CEA.  I will see her with Dr. Omar Muse later this week following her testing and surgical consultation.  Briefly discussed that likely there is a good chance she may need preoperative chemotherapy and radiation followed by surgery later.  She would like to obtain an opinion here from our medical and radiation colleagues if this is indicated.  Discussed she will likely need an abdominal operation unless this is found to be early-stage on the EUS.  Hopefully she would be a candidate for a low-anterior resection.  I did discuss the potential that she may need a diverting loop ileostomy if she needs neoadjuvant therapy.
#2 Hypertension
Well-controlled.
#3 Hyperlipidemia
Well-controlled.
#4 Anemia
Related to No. 1.  We will get an updated CBC today.  I have discussed with her to stop her aspirin completely, and if she needs something before bed, she can take acetaminophen. This is likely contributing obviously to her blood loss and anemia.
#5 Hyperkalemia
We will recheck her potassium and sodium level today prior to her undergoing another bowel prep for the EUS.
#6 GERD
Well-controlled.
#7 Elevated glucose
We will recheck a fasting glucose here to make sure she does not have any problems with impaired glucose tolerance.
#8 PAME
Will get EKG, chest x-ray, and additional LFTs.
#9 Umbilical hernia
Likely this can be fixed if she needs an abdominal operation.  Will discuss with Dr. Muse.  This is minor and is not causing her significant symptoms.
I will see her back with Dr. Muse on Friday.  All questions were answered.  She was seen alone.  Seventy minutes spent.
